{"questionId":"9073300","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">An ideal gas consisting of 0.300 mol undergoes a process ABCD. AB is an adiabatic expansion from the initial volume <em>V</em><sub>A</sub> to the volume 1.5 <em>V</em><sub>A</sub>. BC is an isothermal compression. The pressures at C and D are the same as at A.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/74a83fc586a5ff335e02826a92ab13cd65f992b7.png\"></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The following data are available.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:90px;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Pressure at A = 250 kPa<br>Volume at C &nbsp; = 3.50 × 10<sup>–3</sup> m<sup>3</sup><br>Volume at D &nbsp; = 2.00 × 10<sup>–3</sup> m<sup>3</sup></span></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The gas at C is further compressed to D at a constant pressure. During this compression the temperature decreases by 150 K.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">For the compression CD,</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">determine the thermal energy removed from the system.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 1</strong></em></p>\n<p>work done&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∆</mo><mi>W</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>«</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>»</mo><mn>250</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mo>«</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>»</mo><mn>375</mn><mo> </mo><mo>«</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mo>»</mo></math>&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">✔</span></p>\n<p>change in internal energy&nbsp;<math xmlns